WEBVTT

00:09.042 --> 00:10.532
What's got Daphne all worked up now?

00:11.211 --> 00:12.479
It wasn't Daphne.

00:12.479 --> 00:14.014
It was Maris.

00:14.014 --> 00:15.248
She's gotten involved

00:15.248 --> 00:17.250
with some Argentine polo player.

00:17.250 --> 00:19.047
It turns out he's a gold digger

00:19.219 --> 00:21.050
with a violent temper to boot.

00:21.254 --> 00:22.355
Dr. Crane? Yes?

00:22.355 --> 00:24.050
I'm Esteban di Rojo.

00:25.358 --> 00:28.061
I tell you, Maris will
never come between us again.

00:28.061 --> 00:29.362
MAN: And now, news headlines.

00:29.362 --> 00:33.033
Police have just arrested
Seattle socialite Maris Crane

00:33.033 --> 00:36.730
for the murder of her lover,
polo star Esteban di Rojo.

00:39.105 --> 00:40.140
Oh, come in.

00:40.140 --> 00:41.630
Niles. What have you heard?

00:42.108 --> 00:43.598
Not much. The TV news
is still pretty sketchy.

00:44.110 --> 00:45.111
Dad, did you find anything out?

00:45.111 --> 00:47.113
I called some buddies at the station.

00:47.113 --> 00:48.114
They'll call back when
they know something.

00:48.114 --> 00:50.116
DAPHNE: It's just so freaky.

00:50.116 --> 00:51.618
I can't believe that man is dead.

00:51.618 --> 00:53.609
He was standing right where
you are just a few hours ago.

00:54.120 --> 00:55.121
How you holding up, son?

00:55.121 --> 00:57.624
As well as can be expected.

00:57.624 --> 00:59.626
I meant your brother.

00:59.626 --> 01:02.128
Oh, well, I'm-I'm stunned, of course.

01:02.128 --> 01:05.632
The idea that-that Maris
actually killed someone...

01:05.632 --> 01:08.624
Well, we've all seen her murder
many a lively dinner party.

01:09.169 --> 01:10.570
That's terrible. Frasier.

01:10.570 --> 01:12.572
Oh, come on. I'm joking,

01:12.572 --> 01:14.563
and haven't I earned a
right to my gallows humor?

01:15.275 --> 01:17.277
After all, are you forgetting
that just this afternoon

01:17.277 --> 01:21.145
I was punched in the
face by a man now dead?

01:23.450 --> 01:24.678
Thank you.

01:25.118 --> 01:25.482
Here, drink this.

01:26.186 --> 01:27.187
Oh, thanks.

01:27.187 --> 01:29.189
(phone ringing)

01:29.189 --> 01:30.178
NILES: Hello.

01:30.490 --> 01:32.492
This is he.

01:32.492 --> 01:34.494
Yes, of course.

01:34.494 --> 01:37.197
Uh, I'll be there shortly.

01:37.197 --> 01:38.465
It's the police.

01:38.465 --> 01:40.200
They want to talk to me.

01:40.200 --> 01:41.201
My God, why? They don't suspect you

01:41.201 --> 01:42.502
of anything, do they?

01:42.502 --> 01:43.503
I don't think so.

01:43.503 --> 01:44.504
I don't think they could.

01:44.504 --> 01:46.206
They couldn't, could
they? Dad ? . Calm down.

01:46.206 --> 01:47.507
You had lunch with her today.

01:47.507 --> 01:49.142
They just want to know
what you talked about.

01:49.142 --> 01:50.443
What did we talk about?
What did we talk about?

01:50.443 --> 01:52.206
Uh, let's see. Well...

01:52.445 --> 01:54.504
We-we discussed the upcoming
women's arts festival

01:55.215 --> 01:56.204
and their tableaux vivant.

01:56.516 --> 01:59.212
They're going to be re-enactin
Schmitt's painting of

01:59.519 --> 02:02.215
"The Martyrdom of St.
Ursula by Attila the Hun. "

02:02.522 --> 02:05.225
Naturally, Maris will pose as the Hun.

02:05.225 --> 02:06.419
Ah.

02:06.693 --> 02:07.794
A tad dramatic for my taste,

02:07.794 --> 02:09.795
but nonetheless, I told her I'd help out

02:09.795 --> 02:11.297
by lending her my antique crossbow

02:11.297 --> 02:13.231
to help complete the
tragic scene on the Rhone.

02:13.299 --> 02:14.701
Of course, talk of the Rhone

02:14.701 --> 02:16.669
inevitably led to
that wonderful anecdote

02:17.170 --> 02:19.672
about the Nazarene painters
of Biddlespock Palace.

02:19.672 --> 02:21.674
(guffaws) : Those beer-loving rascals.

02:21.674 --> 02:23.176
Tell it, Niles.

02:23.176 --> 02:24.165
No!

02:26.179 --> 02:28.170
What did she say about the polo guy?

02:28.548 --> 02:30.350
Well, I-I told you,
she-she mentioned

02:30.350 --> 02:31.351
she felt unsafe around him

02:31.351 --> 02:33.353
and that she thought he only wanted her

02:33.353 --> 02:35.622
for her money, and I urged
her to end the relationship.

02:35.622 --> 02:37.624
 Well, that's pretty tame stuff

02:37.624 --> 02:39.319
It'll take more than a little lunch

02:39.626 --> 02:41.227
to tie you into a murder.

02:41.227 --> 02:44.631
Oh, dear. Niles, they're in
front of Maris' house now.

02:44.631 --> 02:47.467
...startling new development
in the society murder case.

02:47.467 --> 02:49.836
Sources say alleged murderer

02:49.836 --> 02:53.239
Maris Crane killed her polo
- playing lover, Esteban di Rojo,

02:53.239 --> 02:54.638
with an antique crossbow.

03:01.347 --> 03:04.217
You gave her the murder weapon.

03:04.217 --> 03:07.209
(telephone ringing)

03:11.224 --> 03:12.725
Hello?

03:12.725 --> 03:14.227
It's a reporter.

03:14.227 --> 03:15.728
I'm not here.

03:15.728 --> 03:17.230
 I'm sorry, he's not here

03:17.230 --> 03:20.233
and I don't know when he's coming back.

03:20.233 --> 03:23.403
I'd rather not say.

03:23.403 --> 03:25.538
I'd rather not say!

03:25.538 --> 03:28.241
Oh, thank you. Manchester, actually.

03:28.241 --> 03:29.230
Hang up.

03:29.342 --> 03:30.410
Good-bye.

03:30.410 --> 03:31.678
NILES: I don't believe this.

03:31.678 --> 03:33.446
It's an unlisted number.

03:33.446 --> 03:35.448
They must think I'm involved somehow.

03:35.448 --> 03:37.450
Th-they're actually
trying to imply that...

03:37.450 --> 03:39.953
(gasping)

03:39.953 --> 03:42.956
No, no, no, I'm not going to panic.

03:42.956 --> 03:45.356
The only way to get through
this is to remain calm.

03:45.525 --> 03:47.584
Right. Now, let's go
on down to the station

03:48.294 --> 03:49.596
and get this all sorted out.

03:49.596 --> 03:50.597
I'm coming, too.

03:50.597 --> 03:52.298
No. You have to rest up

03:52.298 --> 03:54.300
for our doctor's
appointment tomorrow morning.

03:54.300 --> 03:55.289
I'll stay with Daphne.

03:55.602 --> 03:56.603
NILES: Don't worry.

03:56.603 --> 03:59.305
Everything is going to be fine.

03:59.305 --> 04:01.296
(telephone ringing)

04:05.612 --> 04:07.247
You know, that's going
to go on all night.

04:07.247 --> 04:08.236
You want to just stay at my place?

04:08.414 --> 04:10.984
Thanks, but if I let them
drive me out of me own home,

04:10.984 --> 04:11.985
then they've won.

04:11.985 --> 04:12.986
(phone ringing)

04:12.986 --> 04:15.488
Allow me.

04:15.488 --> 04:17.890
Hello?

04:17.890 --> 04:19.791
I see.

04:19.791 --> 04:21.461
Yes, I'll tell her.

04:21.461 --> 04:23.326
Your mother heard the
news. She's on her way over.

